# Styling: Tachyons-First

This project uses **Tachyons v4.12.0** (loaded via CDN). Not Tailwind, not CSS-in-JS. All styling decisions should be made in the mental model of Tachyons.

## Decision Tree (follow this every time)

1. **Can Tachyons do it?** → Use the Tachyons class. Done.
2. **Tachyons can't do it?** → Extend `src/styles/tachyons-ext.css` with a custom utility class that follows Tachyons naming conventions. Done.
3. **Neither works?** → **Stop and ask before proceeding.** Explain why inline styles or custom CSS are needed. Do not silently introduce inline `style={}` or hex values.

## Hard Rules

- **No inline styles.** No `style={{ color: '#ff0000' }}`, no `style={{ maxWidth: '500px' }}`. If a value doesn't exist in Tachyons, create a utility class.
- **No Tailwind.** No `tw-` prefixes, no Tailwind config, no `@apply`. This project does not use Tailwind.
- **No CSS-in-JS.** No styled-components, emotion, or similar.
- **One exception**: JS-driven dynamic styles (animations, randomized values, WebGL, etc.) may use inline styles. Flag these before implementing so they don't creep into regular layout/styling code.

## Extending Tachyons (`tachyons-ext.css`)

When adding to the extension stylesheet, follow Tachyons conventions:

**Colors** — always add the full set:
```css
.{name} { color: #hex; }
.bg-{name} { background-color: #hex; }
.b--{name} { border-color: #hex; }
.hover-{name}:hover { color: #hex; }
.hover-bg-{name}:hover { background-color: #hex; }
```

**Fonts** — register the `@font-face`, then add a utility class:
```css
.font-{name} { font-family: 'Font Name', fallback-stack; }
```

**Custom utilities** — name them like Tachyons would. Short, composable, single-purpose. Examples: `mw5-5`, `hover-br2`, `hide-scrollbar`.

## Baseline Patterns (not rigid rules, just defaults)

- **Base font size**: 22px on `<html>` — all rem-based Tachyons values scale from this
- **Body font**: `.font-system` (Helvetica stack) set on `<body>`
- **Primary text**: `near-black` | **Secondary**: `gray` | **Tertiary**: `silver`, `moon-gray`
- **Links**: typically `blue underline hover-no-underline`
- **Page containers**: `pa4 mw7 center` is the common pattern
- **Type scale**: `f1` display → `f3` page titles → `f4`–`f5` body → `f6` meta/secondary → `f7` captions
- **Spacing**: Tachyons scale (pa1–pa5, ma1–ma5, etc.) — don't invent custom spacing

## Breakpoints

- Tachyons built-in: `-ns` (≥30em), `-m` (30–60em), `-l` (≥60em)
- Custom 700px breakpoint in `tachyons-ext.css`: `dn-md` / `db-md`
- When adding responsive behavior, prefer Tachyons breakpoint suffixes over media queries in component CSS

## Why Tachyons over Tailwind

Tachyons is more legible, lighter, doesn't require a compile step, and lets you tweak styles directly in the browser devtools. The tradeoff (fewer utilities) is handled by extending `tachyons-ext.css` when needed.
